> One extremely versatile and delicious vegetable that's often overlooked is the humble leek. There's so much you can do with this nutritious member of the onion family. In this recipe, it's allowed to really shine, by being braised in a rich sauce along with tender baby carrots.

Pour @water{240%ml} (double for 4p) into a #pot{} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, @paprika{1%sachet} and @vegetable stock{1/2%sachet}.

Bring back to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Pop a lid on the pot and remove from the heat.

Leave aside for ~{12-15%minutes} (or until ready to serve).

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, trim the @leek{1}(trimmed), removing the tough outer layers if necessary. Cut widthways at an angle into 2cm thick slices.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

== Braised Vegetables ==

Place a large pan over high heat (without @oil{a drizzle}).

Once hot, dry-fry the @almonds{15%g}, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from the pan and set aside.

Return the pan to high heat with a @oil{a drizzle}.

Once hot, cook the leek and @baby carrots{150%g} for ~{6-8%minutes}.

Stir only every so often to allow the veg to char.

> TIP: You may need to work in batches to avoid overcrowding the pan.

Reduce the heat to medium.

Add @tomato paste{1%tin}, garlic, @butter{1%tbsp} and @italian herbs{1/2%sachet} (double both for 4p) to the pan.

Toss the veg in the sauce to further caramelise, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the remaining @vegetable stock{1/2%sachet}, @harissa paste{1%sachet}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{150%ml} (double both for 4p) to the pan.

Cover and simmer until veg is tender, ~{5-8%minutes}.

Add a splash of water if you feel the sauce is too thick.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}.

Stir through a @butter{knob}.

> Finish with a sprinkling of scallion and toasted almonds.

== To Serve ==

Divide the paprika bulgur between #bowls{}.

Top with the braised veg.

Crumble over the @Greek style cheese{100%g}.

Finish with a sprinkling of sliced scallion and toasted almonds.